00:15:19,279 --> 00:15:20,240
And that's true.

215
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:31,120
But I realized that even the bigger value of building in public is that you build up a direct channel with the audience and the users that helps you to

216
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,480
build great products.

217
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:36,399
Before building in public, my failure rate was really high.

218
00:15:36,399 --> 00:15:38,320
90% of the things I've done failed.

219
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:40,800
And when I start building in public, it flipped.

220
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:49,600
So now only 10% of my products fail and 90% don't fail because I adjust them before I ship them just because I build in public.

221
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,079
Cool.

222
00:15:50,079 --> 00:15:50,720
I like that.

223
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:54,160
Last question that we'll ask that we ask all founders that come on Starter Story.

224
00:15:54,160 --> 00:16:00,560
If you could stand on John's shoulders when you were getting started with that first bootstrapped that ended up becoming in your whole portfolio,

225
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:04,720
what advice would you give him or anyone building SAS getting started today?

226
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:12,480
The most important thing when you build a startup is the idea and the founder idea fit.

227
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:17,040
So people start looking for random ideas in random spaces and I think that's wrong.

228
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:19,839
I think people should try to build something they understand.

229
00:16:19,839 --> 00:16:24,240
In my case, I went into the extreme and I built things for my own work.

230
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,720
And that's something I understand really really well.

231
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,600
But I think people should build for their own work.

232
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,519
They should solve their own problems.

233
00:16:31,519 --> 00:16:36,959
And I'm sure at any job in the world, there are hundreds of things you can solve with software.

234
00:16:36,959 --> 00:16:38,560
So don't go too far.

235
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,639
Don't look for random things.

236
00:16:40,639 --> 00:16:46,560
Just look around you and see what are the pain points in your job.

237
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,600
Founder market fit.

238
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:54,240
build something that you are passionate about or you have some expert knowledge in and you have such an advantage and such a head start.

239
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:54,880
I love that.

240
